vote.title: To Honor the 30th Anniversary of TECH CORPS
vote.description:
Title
 
To Honor the 30th Anniversary of TECH CORPS
 
Body
 
WHEREAS, TECH CORPS was founded in 1995 with a mission that all K-12 students should have access to high-quality computer science learning experiences; and
 
WHEREAS, TECH CORPS provides programs such as Techie Camp, TECHCORPShack, and Computing Career Corps in five states, including numerous cities and communities; and
 
WHEREAS, these programs are open to all students, focusing primarily on historically underserved and underrepresented communities and students; and
 
WHEREAS, the Ohio programs were launched in 1999; and
 
WHEREAS, in 2011, TECH CORPS moved its headquarters to Columbus, OH; and
 
WHEREAS, in the last 10 years, TECH CORPS has served 22,707 students and 550 educators, while deploying 20,777 volunteers; therefore
 
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE COUNCIL OF THE CITY OF COLUMBUS: That this Council does hereby honor the 30th Anniversary of TECH CORPS.
